From: diaaney <av6cts@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 15 Apr 2026 07:25:31 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] rapier - 1.8 combat: clear use state before sword blockhit to
 survive respawn

the IS_USING entity data flag can end up stuck at true server-side after
a player dies while blocking. respawn does not explicitly clear it and
Paper reuses the same ServerPlayer instance, so on the next right-click
startUsingItem sees flag=true, sets true again (no value change), no
dirty mark, no broadcast. client's LocalPlayer never learns the player
is blocking and the shield pose never renders.

by calling stopUsingItem first for the sword path, the flag transitions
true->false->true within the tick which guarantees the entity data
dirty bit is set, triggering a real broadcast and restoring the client
animation.

diff --git a/net/minecraft/world/item/Item.java b/net/minecraft/world/item/Item.java
index e084af39709951239d15ffe2defd07cde739a72d..e4fdb74675e8b0955bdbb43a5d79b0cfc3a562e0 100644
--- a/net/minecraft/world/item/Item.java
+++ b/net/minecraft/world/item/Item.java
@@ -197,8 +197,11 @@ public class Item implements FeatureElement, ItemLike {
                         return InteractionResult.PASS;
                     }
                 }
-                // rapier - 1.8 combat: force-update using state for swords so switching between swords always rebinds useItem to the currently-held stack (otherwise a stale first-sword useItem blocks a second right-click)
+                // rapier - 1.8 combat: for swords, stop first then start. the explicit false->true transition forces the IS_USING entity-data flag to broadcast. without this, after respawn the server can have a stuck stale flag=true while the client's LocalPlayer believes flag=false, so startUsingItem becomes a no-op broadcast-wise and the blockhit pose never renders.
                 if (itemInHand.is(net.minecraft.tags.ItemTags.SWORDS)) {
+                    if (player.isUsingItem()) {
+                        player.stopUsingItem();
+                    }
                     player.startUsingItem(hand, true);
                 } else {
                     player.startUsingItem(hand);
